Note:
ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE - Typed Process Environment Primitive (Tier 1)

Wraps process environment access. The actual envp string array is
maintained by the host process and made accessible to Runa code via the
syscall-layer environment manager (build_runtime/environment_manager.o).

This module provides the typed-access layer above that:
  - env_get_string  -> typed presence-aware read returning a duplicated
                       string OR a caller-supplied default
  - env_get_integer -> string read + decimal parse + default fallback
  - env_get_bool    -> string read + truthy / falsy normalization
  - env_get_required -> errors if absent

Layout (EnvironmentVariable, 32 bytes):
  offset  0 : name        (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset  8 : value       (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)
  offset 16 : default_val (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)
  offset 24 : present     (8 bytes, 0 = absent, 1 = present)

References:
  - IEEE Std 1003.1 (POSIX) - environment variable conventions
  - Windows _wenviron equivalent on Win64 builds
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/char_core.runa" as Char

Let ENV_VAR_SIZE be 32

Let ENV_ERR_NOT_FOUND be -1
Let ENV_ERR_NULL_NAME be -2

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ENV LOOKUP - PROCESS API
Note: ============================================================================

Note:
The environment lookup callback is supplied by the host runtime. At
bootstrap time the v0.0.8.5 compiler does not yet expose a first-class
getenv-equivalent primitive; the build_runtime environment_manager
object file exports the symbol. This module declares the API surface
and a registration hook so the runtime layer can wire the implementation
without circular imports.

Until the runtime registration is complete, env_lookup_default returns
ENV_ERR_NOT_FOUND. This is the same fallback path callers exercise for
genuinely-absent variables, so production code that only consults
env_get_string_or always gets a usable result.

The registered_callback field is a process-singleton pointer (kept as
an Integer for now since first-class function values do not yet exist
in v0.0.8.5).
:End Note

Let registered_callback be 0

@Reasoning
Register a runtime-provided env_lookup callback. The callback takes a
String name and returns either 0 (not found) or a String pointer the
caller owns. Stored as a singleton so subsequent env_get_* calls
dispatch through it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Store the supplied pointer in the module-level singleton.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Only one callback is registered per process. Registration twice
overwrites the prior pointer - callers must coordinate.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_register_callback" takes callback as Integer returns Integer:
    Set registered_callback to callback
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Default env-lookup used until the runtime callback is registered.
Returns ENV_ERR_NOT_FOUND for every name so callers exercise the
default-fallback paths.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Indirect function calls are not yet first-class in the v0.0.8.5
bootstrap compiler. The registration mechanism exists so future
compiler versions can wire indirect dispatch here. Until then this
routine returns ENV_ERR_NOT_FOUND.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns a sentinel that maps to the safe "not found" path.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_lookup_raw" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return ENV_ERR_NULL_NAME
    End If
    Return ENV_ERR_NOT_FOUND
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPED READS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Read an environment variable as a string, returning a freshly-
duplicated buffer the caller owns. Returns 0 (NULL) if the variable
is unset.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Invoke env_lookup_raw. On ENV_ERR_NOT_FOUND or ENV_ERR_NULL_NAME
return 0. Otherwise duplicate the returned pointer so the caller owns
its copy independent of the runtime's internal storage.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) for the duplicate. Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Environment variables may carry untrusted data; callers must validate
the string before use in security-sensitive contexts (paths, command
arguments, SQL).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_get_string" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let raw be proc env_lookup_raw with name
    If raw is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If raw is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with raw
End Process

@Reasoning
Read an environment variable as a string with a fallback default if
absent. The default string is duplicated so the caller owns the result
unconditionally.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Call env_get_string; if 0, duplicate the default.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Default value is treated as trusted - it is the caller's literal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_get_string_or" takes name as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let v be proc env_get_string with name
    If v is not equal to 0:
        Return v
    End If
    If default_value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with default_value
End Process

@Reasoning
Read an environment variable as a decimal integer with default
fallback. Negative values are supported via a leading '-'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up the raw string. Walk byte-by-byte to validate decimal digits
and optional leading '-'. Accumulate into a 64-bit integer with
overflow checking. On any malformed character return the default.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the string. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strict parse rejects whitespace, leading '+', and trailing characters.
Returns the default on any deviation to prevent silent acceptance of
unusual numeric forms.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_get_integer" takes name as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let raw be proc env_lookup_raw with name
    If raw is less than 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    If raw is equal to 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with raw
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    Let i be 0
    Let is_neg be 0
    Let first be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 0
    If first is equal to 45:
        Set is_neg to 1
        Set i to 1
        If length is equal to 1:
            Return default_value
        End If
    End If
    Let value be 0
    While i is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, i
        Let is_d be proc is_digit from Char with ch
        If is_d is equal to 0:
            Return default_value
        End If
        Set value to value multiplied by 10
        Set value to value plus (ch minus 48)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If is_neg is equal to 1:
        Set value to 0 minus value
    End If
    Return value
End Process

@Reasoning
Read an environment variable as a boolean. Truthy: "1", "true", "yes",
"on" (case-insensitive). Falsy: "0", "false", "no", "off". Anything
else returns the default.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up the raw string. Lowercase via Char.to_lower into a
StringBuilder, then compare against the accepted forms.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the string. Space: O(n) for the lowercased buffer.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strict accepted-form list prevents accidental truthy interpretation
of arbitrary non-empty strings.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_get_bool" takes name as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let raw be proc env_lookup_raw with name
    If raw is less than 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    If raw is equal to 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with raw
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    If length is equal to 1:
        Let c1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 0
        If c1 is equal to 49:
            Return 1
        End If
        If c1 is equal to 48:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return default_value
    End If
    If length is equal to 4:
        Let r0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 0
        Let r1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 1
        Let r2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 2
        Let r3 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 3
        Let a be proc to_lower from Char with r0
        Let b be proc to_lower from Char with r1
        Let c be proc to_lower from Char with r2
        Let d be proc to_lower from Char with r3
        If a is equal to 116:
            If b is equal to 114:
                If c is equal to 117:
                    If d is equal to 101:
                        Return 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If length is equal to 5:
        Let s0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 0
        Let s1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 1
        Let s2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 2
        Let s3 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 3
        Let s4 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 4
        Let a2 be proc to_lower from Char with s0
        Let b2 be proc to_lower from Char with s1
        Let c2 be proc to_lower from Char with s2
        Let d2 be proc to_lower from Char with s3
        Let e2 be proc to_lower from Char with s4
        If a2 is equal to 102:
            If b2 is equal to 97:
                If c2 is equal to 108:
                    If d2 is equal to 115:
                        If e2 is equal to 101:
                            Return 0
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If length is equal to 3:
        Let t0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 0
        Let t1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 1
        Let t2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 2
        Let aa be proc to_lower from Char with t0
        Let bb be proc to_lower from Char with t1
        Let cc be proc to_lower from Char with t2
        If aa is equal to 121:
            If bb is equal to 101:
                If cc is equal to 115:
                    Return 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If aa is equal to 111:
            If bb is equal to 102:
                If cc is equal to 102:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If length is equal to 2:
        Let u0 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 0
        Let u1 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with raw, 1
        Let xa be proc to_lower from Char with u0
        Let xb be proc to_lower from Char with u1
        If xa is equal to 110:
            If xb is equal to 111:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
        If xa is equal to 111:
            If xb is equal to 110:
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Return default_value
End Process

@Reasoning
Read an environment variable that must be present. Returns 0 if absent
- callers should escalate to a fatal-error path on this sentinel.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up; if absent return 0 sentinel.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n) for the duplicate.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Used by bootstrap code that refuses to run without configuration -
typical pattern for production secrets and credentials.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_get_required" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc env_get_string with name
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPED WRAPPER RECORD
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct an EnvironmentVariable wrapper that captures the variable's
current observation - name, present flag, value or default. Used by
bootstrap diagnostics that need to log "which env vars were observed".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Look up the name. Populate the 32-byte record. Duplicate the value or
default into the record's owned slot.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returned record owns its strings and must be freed via env_var_destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_var_capture" takes name as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ev be proc allocate from Layout with ENV_VAR_SIZE
    If ev is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with ev
        Return 0
    End If
    Let actual be proc env_get_string with name
    Let present be 0
    Let default_copy be 0
    If actual is not equal to 0:
        Set present to 1
    Otherwise:
        If default_value is not equal to 0:
            Set default_copy to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with default_value
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ev, 0, name_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ev, 8, actual
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ev, 16, default_copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ev, 24, present
    Return ev
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the captured wrapper and its owned strings.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free name, value, default, then the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_var_destroy" takes ev as Integer returns Integer:
    If ev is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ev, 0
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name
    End If
    Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ev, 8
    If value is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with value
    End If
    Let dflt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ev, 16
    If dflt is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with dflt
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with ev
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
True if the captured variable was present in the process environment.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_var_is_present" takes ev as Integer returns Integer:
    If ev is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ev, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Return the captured value if present, the default otherwise. The
returned string is owned by the captured record - do not free.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
If present, return offset 8. Else return offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returned pointer is alive only while the wrapper is alive.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "env_var_value_or_default" takes ev as Integer returns Integer:
    If ev is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let present be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ev, 24
    If present is equal to 1:
        Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ev, 8
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ev, 16
End Process
